.SH NAME
xcb_destroy_window \- Destroys a window
.SH SYNOPSIS
.hy 0
.B #include <xcb/xproto.h>
.SS Request function
.HP
xcb_void_cookie_t \fBxcb_destroy_window\fP(xcb_connection_t\ *\fIconn\fP, xcb_window_t\ \fIwindow\fP);
.br
.hy 1
.SH REQUEST ARGUMENTS
.IP \fIconn\fP 1i
Da XCB connection ta X11.
.IP \fIwindow\fP 1i
Da window ta destroy.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Destroys tha specified window n' all of its subwindows fo' realz. A DestroyNotify event
is generated fo' each destroyed window (a DestroyNotify event is first generated
for any given windowz inferiors). If tha window was mapped, it will be
automatically unmapped before destroying.

Callin DestroyWindow on tha root window will do nothing.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns a \fIxcb_void_cookie_t\fP. Errors (if any) gotta be handled up in tha event loop.

If you wanna handle errors directly wit \fIxcb_request_check\fP instead, use \fIxcb_destroy_window_checked\fP. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See \fBxcb-requests(3)\fP fo' details.
.SH ERRORS
.IP \fIxcb_window_error_t\fP 1i
Da specified window do not exist.
